Text: What we've done this week.
Similar the previous weeks we had three team meetings, one with Jeremiah and added more functionality to the UI.
We also managed to finally sort out how to merge things together which was relatively simple once we figured out to get it done.
The goodWe were productive adding in features into the UI this week and we are close to adding things to to get a final segmentation and saving the annotations.
We did a decent job of keeping up the productivity while Toto was busy for a few days finishing off work on his lab.
Rara also did a good job working on a lot of working ranging from pre-processing work, merging and JSON file functions.
Things to improve as a teamI feel as a team we've done a decent job on things that needed to be done by prioritising tasks.
The issue this week was I felt some teammates did not take the initiative to tell us what they had been working on.
So I feel I will need to do a better job of checking in on people just to see how they are doing and if they need help.

We also may have gotten to concerned with trying to add in every feature that Jeremiah wanted but I think we have addressed after Friday, deciding on features that we want in the final product in the final week.
Things I could do betterAs mentioned above, I felt I could have done a better job of checking on the team to ask if they needed help or just to see what they were working on.
I feel that some of my team mates have become somewhat stressed out with the project and I felt I didn't really do a good job of having a chat to see how they were.
I feel that this may have caused a little tension with one team member and I hope that if we have a conversation this week we can move forward and help each other.
I'm hoping it's not a major issue going forward and we can sort it out.
Goals for next week.
The goals for the upcoming week are to finish off merge function, finalise a segmentation and then save the information in a JSON file as an output.
There are many things to touch up, but I feel these goals are achievable given the time frame.
General thoughtsÂ .
This week has been a bit rough pushing myself to get more work done, as Toto has been out of action.
This meant a few late nights working on code to get more work done during the week.
However, it has been satisfying getting through obstacles that took a while to figure out as a team.
I hope we can push through as a team and have a enjoyable last week on the project!
